<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="120" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,223,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,539,259,285]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Report associated with sponges:</emphasis>
This species was reported among sponge 
<taxonomicName box="[1025,1164,259,286]" class="Demospongiae" family="Aplysinidae" genus="Aplysina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Verongiida" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[1025,1123,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Aplysina</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
from Rovinj (Rovigno) (Adriatic Sea, Mediterranean Sea) (
<bibRefCitation author="Viets, K." box="[595,721,295,321]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" pagination="1 - 135" refId="ref20734" refString="Viets, K. (1940) Meeresmilben aus der Adria (Halacaridae und Hydrachnellae, Acari). Archiv fur Naturgeschichte, Neue Folge, 9, 1 - 135." type="journal article" year="1940">Viets 1940</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[151,1437,223,465]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,260,331,357]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Remarks</emphasis>
: This has been commonly found in the Mediterranean area (
<bibRefCitation author="Chatterjee, T. &amp; Schizas, N. V. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[960,1214,331,358]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" pagination="527 - 544" refId="ref15154" refString="Chatterjee, T., Schizas, N. V. &amp; Pesic, V. (2019) A checklist of Pontarachnidae (Acari: Hydrachnidia) and notes on distributional patterns of the species. Zootaxa, 4619 (3), 527 - 544. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4619.3.6" type="journal article" year="2019">
Chatterjee 
<emphasis box="[1087,1139,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesic, V. &amp; Durucan, F. &amp; Zawal, A." box="[1227,1425,331,358]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" pagination="501 - 516" refId="ref18862" refString="Pesic, V., Durucan, F. &amp; Zawal, A. (2019) Marine mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia) of the Mediterranean Sea: Descriptions of two new species, key for identification and future prospects. Zootaxa, 4585 (3), 501 - 516. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4585.3.6" type="journal article" year="2019">
Pešić 
<emphasis box="[1296,1348,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
). There are also some records from the Black Sea, 
<collectingCountry box="[760,814,367,393]" name="United States of America" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">USA</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[872,956,367,393]" name="Canada" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Canada</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Chatterjee, T. &amp; Schizas, N. V. &amp; Pesic, V." box="[971,1223,367,393]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" pagination="527 - 544" refId="ref15154" refString="Chatterjee, T., Schizas, N. V. &amp; Pesic, V. (2019) A checklist of Pontarachnidae (Acari: Hydrachnidia) and notes on distributional patterns of the species. Zootaxa, 4619 (3), 527 - 544. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4619.3.6" type="journal article" year="2019">
Chatterjee 
<emphasis box="[1097,1154,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Durucan, F." box="[1243,1436,367,394]" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" pagination="145 - 153" refId="ref15868" refString="Durucan, F. (2021 b) New records of marine water mites (Acari: Hydrachnidia, Pontarachnidae) from Turkey. Persian Journal of Acarology, 10 (2), 145 - 153. https: // doi. org / 10.22073 / pja. v 10 i 2.65665" type="journal article" year="2021">Durucan (2021b)</bibRefCitation>
reported this species from 
<collectingRegion box="[494,554,403,429]" country="Turkey" name="Izmir" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Izmir</collectingRegion>
—Urla-Karantina Island, 
<collectingCountry box="[841,922,403,429]" name="Turkey" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, Aegean Sea among oyster, bivalves 
<taxonomicName authority="(Leach, 1814)" baseAuthorityName="Leach" baseAuthorityYear="1814" class="Bivalvia" family="Margaritidae" genus="Pinctada" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ostreida" pageId="19" pageNumber="120" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="radiata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="120">Pinctada radiata</emphasis>
(Leach, 1814)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
